# Default graphify ignore patterns (all owned projects inherit these)
# Syntax: same as .gitignore

# Build artifacts
dist/
build/
out/
target/

# Dependency dirs
node_modules/
vendor/
.venv/
venv/
__pycache__/
.pytest_cache/

# Logs & temp
*.log
*.tmp
.DS_Store

# graphify itself
graphify-out/

# IDE state
.idea/
.vscode/

# ---- security-specific additions ----
# Even though the security tree is Justin's own content, raw scan output,
# credentials, exploit payloads, and target lists should never enter the
# knowledge graph. Distilled summaries (inventory.md, post-engagement
# notes) are fine — those land in the graph and can flow to the wiki
# with `visibility: internal` on the resulting wiki page.

# Raw outputs and live data
**/scans/
**/output/
**/payloads/
**/captures/
**/loot/
targets.txt
*.pcap
*.pcapng
*.creds
*.hashes
*.nmap
*.gnmap
*.xml.gz

# Anything explicitly marked
*.confidential.*
*.private.*
*.secrets.*
